<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> In game, its the same thing. Those that has the skill will be one step ahead of those that don't. Do that 8th shawl and be the server's first. Sell that PotC set for 15k before the other traders caught up and flood the market. When the next trade-based quest comes along, they'll be ahead of the pack. Its not about recovering the cost by selling what you can make day in day out. Its about having that skill so that you can take advantage for those moments, rip the benefits, then go back to xp.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Which is what I said before... There are three SURE ways to profit, one of which is be there first.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> People do this everyday. People's business is not just about profit and loss. THose that keep going also love that business. I don't see a difference here. In fact, why do you think Povar Tarew Artisans (now &quot;Alliance&quot;) exists. Its for the love, not the profit.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (Didn't they shift away from tradeskills, thus the name change to reflect that?)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Show me a real privately run manufacturing business that operates in the red &quot;everyday&quot; that does NOT fall into either of the categories I listed.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Also, by saying &quot;...subsidised by other income&quot;, you are inferring those that don't do the same are somehow &quot;wronged&quot; by those that do.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->No, I am not. I am saying that these people do not depend on the tradeskill (manufacturing process) to fund itself. This is a basis for the SUBJECT of my writ, why tradeskills are NOT like real world economics.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> There is nothing so pure about trade skill that shouldn't be &quot;contaminated&quot;. In fact, it is the game's vision (omg, did I say that?) for players to level up, kill monsters, and in doing so accumulate wealth. Trade skill is just an alternative form of advancement if you will. It cost a lot of cash.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I pointed out that the way it is run now, you cannot reasonably expect to make a huge profit while skilling up. Hell, I need to go hunt HGs before I go tailoring each week.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> You can profit from tradeskill when you achieve that upper strata. Cultural armors, pottery idols, spiritstones, etc. all are profitable. True, the journey to that point may be costly and unrewarding but hey, if its easy, everyone will be an artisan, no?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->With everybody else undercutting everybody else in the bazaar on finished products, nobody profits. With everybody else gouging everybody else in the bazaar on supplies, the only profiteer is the supplier. As each of these people goes up in level, do you think they will suddenly stop undercutting the other tradeskillers?<br>
<br>
<br>
I stand by my original statement:<br>
