<br>
As for the original post.  Do I choose to pay the prices other players are asking for drop tradeskill items?  No, I do not.  I cannot afford the prices people are asking for the items.  If I had more platinum than time, would I purchase more than I farm?  Certainly, I would.  But in the end, it all comes down to CHOICE.  Whether you agree or disagree with how others raise their skills, keep in mind, that you do not pay their monthy fees to play the game and therefore cannot chose how they spend their time and platinum.  Nor can you force others to set prices higher or lower depending on your standards.  The most you can do, is offer what YOU CHOOSE to pay and set your prices at what YOU CHOOSE to charge.  I personally have found that most of the time there is a middle ground where both sides at least break even.<br>
<br>
