Also in response to the topic at hand.  A lot of the higher tradeskill components require massive amounts of items to skill up on.  Most of the items in the higher end of the skills require these items in so much massive quantities that it would take days on end just to receive enough of the components to push enough combines for a skill up.  When most people buy the components at inflated prices it is not because they are paying for the components.  It is because of the time involved to get the components vs the time it would take to farm the plat/components them self. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.povartarewalliance.org/roster/index.shtml?action=preview&amp;charname=Mattron&amp;showAlts=false" target="top"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;font-size:x-small;">Mattron Stellarwind</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:black;font-size:xx-small;"> - Level 51 Channeler of Xev </span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
